note right of users
    **User Roles & Permissions:**
    
    STUDENT:
    - View enrolled courses
    - Submit assignments
    - View grades & feedback
    - Track progress
    - Send/receive messages
    
    INSTRUCTOR:
    - Manage own courses (CRUD)
    - Upload materials
    - View enrolled students
    - Grade submissions
    - Generate reports
    
    ADMIN:
    - Full system access
    - User management (create/delete)
    - Course approvals
    - System configuration
    - Audit log access
end note

note right of courses
    **Course Lifecycle:**
    
    1. PENDING: Created by instructor, awaiting admin approval
    2. ACTIVE: Approved, visible to students, enrollments open
    3. ARCHIVED: Past term, no new enrollments
    4. REJECTED: Didn't meet requirements, feedback provided
    
    **Constraints:**
    - Capacity limit on enrollments
    - Cannot delete if has active students
    - Status transitions controlled by role
end note

note right of assignments
    **Assignment Status Flow:**
    
    PENDING → SUBMITTED → GRADED
           ↓
         OVERDUE (if deadline passed)
    
    **Data Cascading:**
    - Grade stored in both Assignments & Submissions
    - Used to calculate course GPA
    - Enrollment grade calculated from all assignments
end note

note bottom of audit
    **Audit Trail:**
    Every CREATE/UPDATE/DELETE operation logged:
    - Who changed it (user_id)
    - When it happened (timestamp)
    - What changed (old_value → new_value)
    - Optional: IP address for security
    
    **Retention:** 7 years (compliance requirement)
end note

@enduml
